BAUCHI – Communities in Bauchi state have lauded the former Speaker of the House of Representative, Yakubu Dogara for donating food items to Muslims umma at Ramadan. Alhaji Bappah Audu, who spoke to Journalists on behalf of the benefiting communities of the 20 local government areas in Bauchi said that the benefiting communities commended Dogara for the donation of food items during the fasting period when people need it most and as well promote good relationships. “On behalf of the benefiting communities we are grateful to the former Speaker.We appreciate him for his passion for helping the poor and working for the development of the state.The beneficiaries are mosques, chief Imam’s, less privileged, various associations and the downtrodden at Ramadan. -Advertisement- “The food items distributed include 4 Trailers of Rice. 1 Trailer load of Sugar, 2 Trailers of assorted grains.300 cartons of spaghetti, Can fish400 cartons of Indomie Noodles. “35% of the consignment went to his Federal Constituency while the balance of 65% went to the remaining 17LGAs in the State,” he said. The former Speaker Dogara is the member representing the Bogoro/Dass/Tafawa-Balewa Federal Constituency at the National Assembly.